        "content": "<p>macovedj opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13948\">PR #13948</a> from <code>macovedj:winch-aarch64-v128-abi</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>While observing which tests flip as we add simd instructions for <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/9925\">https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/9925</a>, it became clear that while the instructions become usable, the simd types still error <code>Unsupported Wasm Type</code> when they appear in function signatures.  I was able to reproduce the logic in <code>to_abi_operand</code> from the x64 implementation to use vector registers and larger stack slots for V128.  This removes the error from the included .wat files, and flips a number of tests that should have flipped from the simd instructions that have been implemented so far.</p>\n</blockquote>",
